MOTHER’S DAY ✨ I thought I never wanted children. I had a hard time being around children, I had extremely untreated stuff around my own childhood that would always come up around kids so I avoided them. I also believed in my core that I didn’t deserve to have them, that I was too broken to be able to do this. The pandemic happened, and it broke me. I sold the shop and with it who I thought I was. So I went back to meetings (what you put before your program you certainly do loose) and I finally got on the right psych meds after decades of trying and quitting (I am no longer afraid of fire 🥴) and most importantly I checked into a place and did intensive childhood trauma work. The last day they suggested finding ways to be around children to experience joy. I knew in that moment I was no longer too ashamed to have a child or too scared. I came home and told that to Levi, not thinking that we’d have one, but just stoked on that much growth. Six months later I jokingly told him he was gonna have to let me adopt one of these cats I was looking at online or give me a baby. Six weeks after that we were pregnant. My pregnancy was hard and scary. My postpartum has been very hard physically, but oh my god did my heart grow three sizes the day Zoë came into our world. My heart feels like it’s going to explode out of my chest when I hold her. I cannot wait to show her all the things that were beautiful about my childhood, and have her show me all the things that will be beautiful about hers. Thank you universe for her, thank you @levioner for being the best daddy she could ask for, I can’t wait for the grin I’ll give you when she asks you if we can adopt a cat 😸 it’s never too late to be the person you could have been ✨ thank you to all the mommas and grandmommas that are in our life as well 📷 @travishaight

21✨ I’ve now been sober longer than I had been alive when I got sober. 21 years ago, after trying for almost a year to quit, I finally was able to string some days together. My life truly is beyond my wildest dreams. I never thought I’d live this long, or have a family of my own, or feel this free. I owe it all to the coffee club people who came before me for helping me one day at a time, and in recent years the outside specialists who have helped me through my anxiety with therapy and psych meds. I didn’t do it alone, but no one did it for me. If you’re struggling and want to reach out, I’d love to talk to you. It’s never too late to be the person you could’ve been. ✨ (also this could be a post about my aesthetic procedures over the years 😂 and if you’ve got questions about that I’m open about that too, my skin and my sobriety have taken a village 🫠)
